WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.177 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:09.177 --> 00:00:11.010 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Let's
go into the essence

00:00:11.010 --> 00:00:14.440 align:middle line:10%
of five of the missing chapters,
and including this symbol.

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:16.950 align:middle line:10%
>>STEVEN ROSS: I brought the
dream to Pearl, and she gasped.

00:00:16.950 --> 00:00:20.820 align:middle line:10%
She goes, oh, I think
Mr. Hall should see this.

00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:24.390 align:middle line:84%
He looks at me and
he goes, who are you?

00:00:24.390 --> 00:00:27.900 align:middle line:84%
It isn't about what political
party you belong to.

00:00:27.900 --> 00:00:30.960 align:middle line:84%
It isn't about what
religion you belong to.

00:00:30.960 --> 00:00:33.890 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:00:33.890 --> 00:00:39.330 align:middle line:90%


00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:42.060 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: As we see society
losing its bearings in terms

00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:44.400 align:middle line:10%
of discernment and
truth, we can find sanity

00:00:44.400 --> 00:00:47.160 align:middle line:10%
in some of the ancient
mysteries of times past.

00:00:47.160 --> 00:00:50.280 align:middle line:84%
Manly P. Hall dedicated his
life to the preservation

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:53.010 align:middle line:84%
and perpetuation of
the great teachings

00:00:53.010 --> 00:00:56.310 align:middle line:84%
in his book, The Secret
Teachings of All Ages.

00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:59.700 align:middle line:10%
Our guest today, Stephen
Ross, spent time with Hall

00:00:59.700 --> 00:01:01.860 align:middle line:10%
and had the profound
gift of being allowed

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:05.459 align:middle line:10%
into his private vault of
documents, where he found

00:01:05.459 --> 00:01:07.950 align:middle line:10%
unknown works by Manly P. Hall.

00:01:07.950 --> 00:01:09.990 align:middle line:90%
I mean, this is a big deal.

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:15.720 align:middle line:84%
This is 1928, almost 100
years ago, when he wrote this.

00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:18.690 align:middle line:84%
People don't understand,
Manly was a young man,

00:01:18.690 --> 00:01:22.960 align:middle line:84%
but he was downloading from
other realms and lifetimes

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:23.760 align:middle line:90%
of knowledge.

00:01:23.760 --> 00:01:28.200 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to go into
how you ended up in his sphere

00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:31.680 align:middle line:84%
and in his vaults, and then
surprise everybody with what

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:33.210 align:middle line:90%
follows.

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:34.150 align:middle line:90%
Welcome back, Steven.

00:01:34.150 --> 00:01:35.280 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Thank you, Regina.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:39.120 align:middle line:10%
I always appreciate you
inviting me here and allowing

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:40.740 align:middle line:10%
me to share with your audience.

00:01:40.740 --> 00:01:42.120 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Oh, I love it.

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:44.845 align:middle line:84%
It's always so-- you know,
I always close my eyes

00:01:44.845 --> 00:01:47.220 align:middle line:84%
and take a little breath just
before the camera comes on.

00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:48.870 align:middle line:84%
And whenever you're
here, it's just

00:01:48.870 --> 00:01:51.470 align:middle line:84%
there's so much heart
energy, and besides all

00:01:51.470 --> 00:01:53.970 align:middle line:84%
of the kind of massive
light around the top side.

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:54.810 align:middle line:90%
I just love it.

00:01:54.810 --> 00:01:55.610 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Thank you.

00:01:55.610 --> 00:01:59.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's
start in the late 1970s,

00:01:59.790 --> 00:02:04.960 align:middle line:84%
when you went to a Friday
night lecture in Los Angeles.

00:02:04.960 --> 00:02:05.760 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Yes.

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:08.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Where Manly P.
Hall centered his work.

00:02:08.370 --> 00:02:09.960 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Correct.

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:14.880 align:middle line:10%
I really was introduced to
the esoteric metaphysical

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:18.000 align:middle line:10%
information in 1974.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:20.820 align:middle line:10%
And in 1978, someone
mentioned to me

00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:26.310 align:middle line:10%
about a great philosopher, Manly
P. Hall, and his Philosophical

00:02:26.310 --> 00:02:32.070 align:middle line:10%
Research Society, an incredible
place, 50,000 volumes

00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:35.220 align:middle line:10%
with materials dated to BC.

00:02:35.220 --> 00:02:40.470 align:middle line:84%
So I wandered down to the
center on a Friday night Lyceum,

00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:44.580 align:middle line:84%
and there were about
70 people in this room.

00:02:44.580 --> 00:02:47.910 align:middle line:84%
Now I was not the
bravest of individuals

00:02:47.910 --> 00:02:50.760 align:middle line:84%
with my math science
background in sports,

00:02:50.760 --> 00:02:55.410 align:middle line:84%
wandering into a philosophy
place and esoteric.

00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:58.620 align:middle line:84%
So I did what I
did in that time.

00:02:58.620 --> 00:03:01.800 align:middle line:84%
I went way in the back,
sat in the last row.

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.535 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A little
coward in your 20s.

00:03:03.535 --> 00:03:04.410 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: There you go.

00:03:04.410 --> 00:03:06.270 align:middle line:90%
Just a fly on the wall.

00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:09.690 align:middle line:84%
And in the front of the
room was a blackboard.

00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:12.330 align:middle line:84%
There were six
sentences written.

00:03:12.330 --> 00:03:14.850 align:middle line:84%
And in the front were
three individuals

00:03:14.850 --> 00:03:17.190 align:middle line:90%
who were the moderators.

00:03:17.190 --> 00:03:20.520 align:middle line:84%
There was two gentlemen
who I later would find out

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:24.210 align:middle line:84%
had followed Mr. Hall
for about 35 years,

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:26.800 align:middle line:84%
and then a woman
named Pearl Thomas,

00:03:26.800 --> 00:03:32.100 align:middle line:84%
who was the personal
librarian at the PRS.

00:03:32.100 --> 00:03:40.860 align:middle line:84%
And they would answer questions
of the previous Sunday's Mr.

00:03:40.860 --> 00:03:41.670 align:middle line:90%
Hall lecture.

00:03:41.670 --> 00:03:42.760 align:middle line:90%
Every Sunday he lectured.

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:43.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:03:43.560 --> 00:03:44.970 align:middle line:90%
Then the following Friday night.

00:03:44.970 --> 00:03:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: They would discuss
six or seven points.

00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:51.570 align:middle line:84%
So the meeting was going along,
and somebody in the audience

00:03:51.570 --> 00:03:55.350 align:middle line:84%
asked the moderators, what
about point number six?

00:03:55.350 --> 00:04:00.480 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden Pearl Thomas
raises up her hand and points

00:04:00.480 --> 00:04:04.750 align:middle line:84%
into the audience, and she
was pointing right at me.

00:04:04.750 --> 00:04:07.920 align:middle line:84%
And I could see people
shifting their position so she

00:04:07.920 --> 00:04:09.910 align:middle line:90%
wouldn't be pointing at them.

00:04:09.910 --> 00:04:12.810 align:middle line:90%
And the next thing I remember--

00:04:12.810 --> 00:04:14.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the crowd
parted and the finger's

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:15.240 align:middle line:90%
pointing at you.

00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:16.829 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: The seas
parted, and there it

00:04:16.829 --> 00:04:18.870 align:middle line:90%
was, the finger pointed at me.

00:04:18.870 --> 00:04:21.329 align:middle line:90%
And I'm thinking, what is this?

00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:24.610 align:middle line:90%
But I ended up speaking.

00:04:24.610 --> 00:04:26.520 align:middle line:90%
I did not remember what I said.

00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:31.380 align:middle line:84%
But when I finished,
everybody was looking at me.

00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:35.550 align:middle line:84%
And it just so happened after
that, the group broke up,

00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:37.350 align:middle line:90%
and I was looking to leave.

00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:41.640 align:middle line:84%
Pearl Thomas, who I found
out she was in her late 80s,

00:04:41.640 --> 00:04:46.140 align:middle line:84%
had been with Mr.
Hall for 60 years.

00:04:46.140 --> 00:04:50.520 align:middle line:84%
She says to me, how long have
you been studying Mr. Hall?

00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:52.170 align:middle line:90%
How many books have you read?

00:04:52.170 --> 00:04:54.330 align:middle line:84%
I said, I've never
read any of his books.

00:04:54.330 --> 00:04:57.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, how many lectures
have you attended?

00:04:57.270 --> 00:05:00.000 align:middle line:90%
I have never heard him lecture.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.697 align:middle line:90%
And she said to me, young man--

00:05:02.697 --> 00:05:04.530 align:middle line:84%
because I was young
then, back in the '70s--

00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: In your 20s, yeah.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.230 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: Please
visit me tomorrow,

00:05:08.230 --> 00:05:10.540 align:middle line:90%
Saturday, in the library.

00:05:10.540 --> 00:05:13.470 align:middle line:84%
So the next day I
go into the library.

00:05:13.470 --> 00:05:14.790 align:middle line:90%
Magnificent.

00:05:14.790 --> 00:05:18.330 align:middle line:84%
Regina, 50,000 books
all behind glass.

00:05:18.330 --> 00:05:21.870 align:middle line:84%
You would find a book,
talk to the librarian,

00:05:21.870 --> 00:05:25.230 align:middle line:84%
she would open it with a
key, you would read it,

00:05:25.230 --> 00:05:26.980 align:middle line:90%
and then it's returned.

00:05:26.980 --> 00:05:32.050 align:middle line:84%
So I spent that day in
this incredible place.

00:05:32.050 --> 00:05:38.950 align:middle line:84%
And then after my third visit,
Pearl Thomas said to me,

00:05:38.950 --> 00:05:42.330 align:middle line:84%
you just open up, you
take the books out.

00:05:42.330 --> 00:05:43.380 align:middle line:90%
I trust you.

00:05:43.380 --> 00:05:48.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, that night I had a dream
and I wrote the dream down.

00:05:48.330 --> 00:05:51.690 align:middle line:84%
And you and I have had shows
before talking about dreams,

00:05:51.690 --> 00:05:53.370 align:middle line:90%
and dreams have guided me.

00:05:53.370 --> 00:05:56.310 align:middle line:84%
So I brought the dream
to Pearl, and she gasps.

00:05:56.310 --> 00:06:01.260 align:middle line:84%
She goes, oh, I think
Mr. Hall should see this.

00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:04.650 align:middle line:84%
So she apparently
gave it to Mr. Hall.

00:06:04.650 --> 00:06:08.640 align:middle line:84%
And three days
later, he calls me up

00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:10.620 align:middle line:90%
and invites me to visit him.

00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:14.880 align:middle line:84%
Now Mr. Hall was in such
demand that nobody really could

00:06:14.880 --> 00:06:16.020 align:middle line:90%
get appointments with him.

00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:16.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:06:16.890 --> 00:06:21.270 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: And it was very funny
because people, I was told,

00:06:21.270 --> 00:06:25.560 align:middle line:84%
would call and say, this is
Plato, this is Jesus Christ,

00:06:25.560 --> 00:06:27.240 align:middle line:90%
I would love to meet Mr. Hall.

00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:30.840 align:middle line:84%
So they were screaming, and
nobody was getting in there.

00:06:30.840 --> 00:06:33.490 align:middle line:84%
But he calls me
up, and I meet him.

00:06:33.490 --> 00:06:36.040 align:middle line:84%
And just as you and I are
looking at each other,

00:06:36.040 --> 00:06:39.600 align:middle line:84%
he looks at me and
he goes, who are you?

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:41.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's the
big fat question, isn't it?

00:06:41.850 --> 00:06:43.050 align:middle line:90%
Who is Steven Ross?

00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:44.850 align:middle line:90%
Well, I have some ideas.

00:06:44.850 --> 00:06:47.220 align:middle line:84%
But you are a
unique human being.

00:06:47.220 --> 00:06:50.670 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: And I said,
I am a student.

00:06:50.670 --> 00:06:53.760 align:middle line:90%
And he said, why have you come?

00:06:53.760 --> 00:06:59.610 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I want to get
into your personal vault.

00:06:59.610 --> 00:07:02.048 align:middle line:90%
And he said, OK.

00:07:02.048 --> 00:07:03.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Just like that.

00:07:03.090 --> 00:07:04.048 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Just like that.

00:07:04.048 --> 00:07:08.070 align:middle line:84%
And the reason he did was
because his Philosophical

00:07:08.070 --> 00:07:12.150 align:middle line:84%
Research Society
was built in 1934.

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:18.330 align:middle line:84%
My dream was how he
wanted to build the PRS,

00:07:18.330 --> 00:07:20.610 align:middle line:84%
but he did not
have enough money.

00:07:20.610 --> 00:07:22.320 align:middle line:90%
And he, of course--

00:07:22.320 --> 00:07:25.650 align:middle line:90%
this would be in the 1920s--

00:07:25.650 --> 00:07:28.500 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't born until
1949, so he knew

00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:30.420 align:middle line:90%
there was no way I could know.

00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:34.230 align:middle line:84%
It was a calling card
from my spiritual sources

00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:38.340 align:middle line:84%
that allowed me to go
into his personal vault,

00:07:38.340 --> 00:07:42.390 align:middle line:84%
not the 50,000 books,
but his personal vault,

00:07:42.390 --> 00:07:51.240 align:middle line:84%
and xerox what I wanted to do,
with the proviso I would never

00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:55.590 align:middle line:84%
sell any of those books that
I found in there while he

00:07:55.590 --> 00:08:01.020 align:middle line:84%
was alive because his society
was reprinting old books.

00:08:01.020 --> 00:08:03.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But the point
was that he saw you,

00:08:03.840 --> 00:08:06.960 align:middle line:84%
he saw you who you really
are, and he trusted you

00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:08.940 align:middle line:84%
because of the
ethics of your being,

00:08:08.940 --> 00:08:11.430 align:middle line:84%
and also the deep, deep,
deep knowledge that you

00:08:11.430 --> 00:08:12.270 align:middle line:90%
bring through.

00:08:12.270 --> 00:08:13.070 align:middle line:90%
And you have.

00:08:13.070 --> 00:08:15.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you've been doing
this your whole life.

00:08:15.030 --> 00:08:17.700 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, that's
what happened that day.

00:08:17.700 --> 00:08:19.450 align:middle line:84%
When you say you don't
know what you said,

00:08:19.450 --> 00:08:22.290 align:middle line:84%
you streamed some apparently
pertinent information

00:08:22.290 --> 00:08:24.150 align:middle line:84%
through that the
group took notice of.

00:08:24.150 --> 00:08:28.080 align:middle line:84%
And so he already knew because
he has the same abilities,

00:08:28.080 --> 00:08:31.530 align:middle line:84%
so he was primed to meet
with you and to trust you.

00:08:31.530 --> 00:08:35.370 align:middle line:84%
So you started
photocopying, including

00:08:35.370 --> 00:08:37.740 align:middle line:90%
ancient, ancient parchments.

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:42.530 align:middle line:84%
And as I read in the
foreword of the book--

00:08:42.530 --> 00:08:45.630 align:middle line:84%
no, the introduction-- you
wrote that you actually

00:08:45.630 --> 00:08:49.890 align:middle line:84%
incurred some eyesight
damage at the time

00:08:49.890 --> 00:08:52.200 align:middle line:90%
as a result of the photocopying.

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:58.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: Of course, because I was
taking books written in 1620,

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:04.020 align:middle line:84%
1650, 1700, walking out of the
vault, walking down a corridor

00:09:04.020 --> 00:09:06.390 align:middle line:84%
and putting them
on a xerox machine,

00:09:06.390 --> 00:09:10.560 align:middle line:84%
praying that the bindings
wouldn't break as I was

00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:13.710 align:middle line:90%
xeroxing each page one by one.

00:09:13.710 --> 00:09:16.440 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the
interesting story was

00:09:16.440 --> 00:09:19.620 align:middle line:84%
when I did it the very first
time, the very first book,

00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:23.340 align:middle line:84%
I walk out of the vault.
And the business manager

00:09:23.340 --> 00:09:26.750 align:middle line:84%
of the Philosophical
Research Society, this woman

00:09:26.750 --> 00:09:27.550 align:middle line:90%
went nuclear.

00:09:27.550 --> 00:09:30.000 align:middle line:84%
She had never seen or
heard of me before.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:32.380 align:middle line:84%
And she goes, what
are you doing,

00:09:32.380 --> 00:09:34.530 align:middle line:84%
and literally grabbed
me by my collar.

00:09:34.530 --> 00:09:37.170 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to put you in
the room with Mr. Hall.

00:09:37.170 --> 00:09:39.360 align:middle line:90%
Well, she put me in there.

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:40.230 align:middle line:90%
He looks at me.

00:09:40.230 --> 00:09:41.880 align:middle line:90%
I look at him.

00:09:41.880 --> 00:09:44.320 align:middle line:84%
I said, I'm just doing
what we discussed.

00:09:44.320 --> 00:09:45.120 align:middle line:90%
Fine.

00:09:45.120 --> 00:09:47.010 align:middle line:90%
I walk out.

00:09:47.010 --> 00:09:49.565 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what she expected,
but I just looked at her.

00:09:49.565 --> 00:09:51.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Thought you were
going to get a spanking.

00:09:51.690 --> 00:09:53.730 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: I really
do believe that.

00:09:53.730 --> 00:09:58.110 align:middle line:90%
And I was a little uppity.

00:09:58.110 --> 00:09:59.610 align:middle line:90%
I was like that then.

00:09:59.610 --> 00:10:03.870 align:middle line:84%
But I just said, no, I'm
just going to continue.

00:10:03.870 --> 00:10:07.830 align:middle line:84%
My eyes would kind
of be turned away,

00:10:07.830 --> 00:10:12.510 align:middle line:84%
but that xerox light,
I xeroxed about 30

00:10:12.510 --> 00:10:16.560 align:middle line:84%
ancient alchemical texts,
some manuscripts that

00:10:16.560 --> 00:10:18.900 align:middle line:90%
have never been printed.

00:10:18.900 --> 00:10:23.643 align:middle line:84%
With that opportunity, I really
was there about five months.

00:10:23.643 --> 00:10:25.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean, what's
amazing is, and we'll

00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:29.100 align:middle line:84%
get to that later, but you now
possess what someone called

00:10:29.100 --> 00:10:32.220 align:middle line:84%
the new Manly P. Hall modern
day library because yours

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:36.270 align:middle line:84%
is very similar, this incredible
library that you have.

00:10:36.270 --> 00:10:38.492 align:middle line:90%
We were talking off camera.

00:10:38.492 --> 00:10:39.950 align:middle line:84%
We've been friends
for a long time.

00:10:39.950 --> 00:10:43.660 align:middle line:84%
But book merchants
will come around

00:10:43.660 --> 00:10:46.510 align:middle line:84%
and start salivating when they
see what you have in there,

00:10:46.510 --> 00:10:48.560 align:middle line:90%
some of it under glass also.

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:50.050 align:middle line:90%
Very, very ancient.

00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:54.145 align:middle line:84%
And so do you think that it
was your exposure to Manly P.

00:10:54.145 --> 00:10:57.850 align:middle line:84%
Hall's library that really
gave you kind of the impetus

00:10:57.850 --> 00:11:00.160 align:middle line:84%
and imbued you with
the desire to create

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:04.180 align:middle line:84%
this library of your own,
this amazing material?

00:11:04.180 --> 00:11:07.540 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: I would like to say yes.

00:11:07.540 --> 00:11:13.480 align:middle line:84%
But I will say that I always
had this innate feeling,

00:11:13.480 --> 00:11:17.363 align:middle line:84%
and I've also had numerous
past lives that I've been--

00:11:17.363 --> 00:11:18.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A librarian?

00:11:18.280 --> 00:11:19.483 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: A librarian.

00:11:19.483 --> 00:11:20.650 align:middle line:90%
How did you ever guess that?

00:11:20.650 --> 00:11:22.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because you
call yourself a librarian.

00:11:22.650 --> 00:11:25.190 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: I'm just a librarian,
but I have done it before.

00:11:25.190 --> 00:11:29.590 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you what I did
pick up from Manly Hall.

00:11:29.590 --> 00:11:31.750 align:middle line:84%
Manly hall had
more books in print

00:11:31.750 --> 00:11:35.870 align:middle line:84%
than any living author
while he was alive.

00:11:35.870 --> 00:11:37.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's
saying something, including

00:11:37.870 --> 00:11:39.100 align:middle line:90%
Rudolph Steiner and others.

00:11:39.100 --> 00:11:41.740 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Absolutely.

00:11:41.740 --> 00:11:44.600 align:middle line:90%
It was the way that he wrote.

00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:48.100 align:middle line:84%
He never really wrote
books on phenomena.

00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:50.830 align:middle line:84%
His goal was how
individuals could

00:11:50.830 --> 00:11:56.980 align:middle line:84%
live a more balanced, loving,
beautiful life because people

00:11:56.980 --> 00:11:59.170 align:middle line:84%
can be into the phenomena,
but that doesn't

00:11:59.170 --> 00:12:00.430 align:middle line:90%
mean that they're happy.

00:12:00.430 --> 00:12:02.320 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean
that they're healthy.

00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:07.310 align:middle line:84%
Manly Hall wrote with such
beauty on a variety of topics.

00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:11.320 align:middle line:84%
What I picked up from
him was the understanding

00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:18.790 align:middle line:84%
that it isn't about how much an
individual knows that you meet.

00:12:18.790 --> 00:12:23.110 align:middle line:84%
It is how you unfold
within your own self.

00:12:23.110 --> 00:12:25.690 align:middle line:84%
And throughout all
of his writings,

00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:30.950 align:middle line:84%
he never is encouraging
people to follow his way.

00:12:30.950 --> 00:12:36.010 align:middle line:84%
So what I picked up was just
an incredible understanding

00:12:36.010 --> 00:12:40.180 align:middle line:84%
that all of these materials
that are written that are really

00:12:40.180 --> 00:12:44.890 align:middle line:84%
of a profound nature are
encouraging individuals

00:12:44.890 --> 00:12:48.970 align:middle line:84%
to unfold and
unflower themselves.

00:12:48.970 --> 00:12:54.280 align:middle line:84%
There is too many egos
existing in this field, people

00:12:54.280 --> 00:12:57.920 align:middle line:84%
who will go and say,
oh, anybody can do it.

00:12:57.920 --> 00:12:59.840 align:middle line:84%
But if you really
listen to them,

00:12:59.840 --> 00:13:03.940 align:middle line:84%
they're encouraging you to have
to come to them because only

00:13:03.940 --> 00:13:06.040 align:middle line:90%
they have the answer.

00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:09.820 align:middle line:84%
And it was interesting to note
in the materials I learned

00:13:09.820 --> 00:13:14.350 align:middle line:84%
from Mr. Hall was where
he said, what I've written

00:13:14.350 --> 00:13:17.960 align:middle line:84%
may seem contradictory
sometimes.

00:13:17.960 --> 00:13:23.840 align:middle line:84%
But everything, its intent is
to point you in a direction.

00:13:23.840 --> 00:13:27.580 align:middle line:84%
I am never going to give you
the answers, he would say.

00:13:27.580 --> 00:13:30.950 align:middle line:84%
But my intent is to point
you in the direction.

00:13:30.950 --> 00:13:32.170 align:middle line:90%
So I made a vow.

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:36.340 align:middle line:84%
That is the strongest thing
that came out of my experience

00:13:36.340 --> 00:13:37.840 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:42.550 align:middle line:84%
My vow is to encourage
people to help

00:13:42.550 --> 00:13:45.820 align:middle line:84%
them see what their
own potential is,

00:13:45.820 --> 00:13:50.420 align:middle line:84%
to light up the area around
them and let you know everything

00:13:50.420 --> 00:13:52.630 align:middle line:90%
that's possible for you.

00:13:52.630 --> 00:13:56.620 align:middle line:84%
Or another analogy I use is,
I'm like a bus stop bench.

00:13:56.620 --> 00:14:00.010 align:middle line:84%
People will come, will
share, but they're

00:14:00.010 --> 00:14:02.200 align:middle line:84%
going to go on their
bus route, and I'm

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:04.540 align:middle line:90%
going to go on my bus route.

00:14:04.540 --> 00:14:07.690 align:middle line:84%
But during that time,
we've exchanged.

00:14:07.690 --> 00:14:11.170 align:middle line:84%
That is what was
the most impactful.

00:14:11.170 --> 00:14:15.310 align:middle line:84%
And so the library that I have,
hopefully it's the same way.

00:14:15.310 --> 00:14:18.220 align:middle line:84%
When people come,
what I tell them is,

00:14:18.220 --> 00:14:22.160 align:middle line:84%
I am just going to talk
about different sections.

00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:24.850 align:middle line:84%
You don't even have to keep
up with me as I circle.

00:14:24.850 --> 00:14:26.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to keep talking.

00:14:26.530 --> 00:14:32.380 align:middle line:84%
If something appeals to you,
you stop and you look at it,

00:14:32.380 --> 00:14:35.020 align:middle line:84%
and I just go about
my way talking.

00:14:35.020 --> 00:14:40.630 align:middle line:84%
And they may be five bookcases
back in another section.

00:14:40.630 --> 00:14:44.200 align:middle line:84%
These are the profound
people, I believe,

00:14:44.200 --> 00:14:47.830 align:middle line:84%
on this planet, Regina,
are the ones that don't

00:14:47.830 --> 00:14:50.150 align:middle line:90%
encourage us to follow them.

00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:50.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:14:50.950 --> 00:14:55.030 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: They encourage us
to be within our own selves.

00:14:55.030 --> 00:14:57.610 align:middle line:90%
There is an old saying.

00:14:57.610 --> 00:15:04.370 align:middle line:84%
If we follow wise people,
we weaken ourselves.

00:15:04.370 --> 00:15:08.830 align:middle line:84%
But if we follow ourselves,
we become wise people.

00:15:08.830 --> 00:15:10.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Very truly said.

00:15:10.360 --> 00:15:13.030 align:middle line:84%
Before we get into
this, what you

00:15:13.030 --> 00:15:17.080 align:middle line:84%
were able to photograph in the
vault, has much of it come out?

00:15:17.080 --> 00:15:19.870 align:middle line:84%
Because we're going to talk
about some major information

00:15:19.870 --> 00:15:22.600 align:middle line:84%
that was in that vault
that's just now coming out,

00:15:22.600 --> 00:15:25.370 align:middle line:84%
literally 92 years
after it was written.

00:15:25.370 --> 00:15:26.170 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Right.

00:15:26.170 --> 00:15:28.212 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Was there quite
a bit of that in there?

00:15:28.212 --> 00:15:31.030 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: Well, some of
the old alchemical books

00:15:31.030 --> 00:15:34.030 align:middle line:90%
have been reprinted now.

00:15:34.030 --> 00:15:38.620 align:middle line:84%
When I did the
xeroxing in '78, '79.

00:15:38.620 --> 00:15:40.210 align:middle line:90%
We just didn't have that.

00:15:40.210 --> 00:15:44.320 align:middle line:84%
Now quite a lot of
reprints come out of India,

00:15:44.320 --> 00:15:46.960 align:middle line:84%
and they come out with
beautiful leather binding

00:15:46.960 --> 00:15:48.460 align:middle line:90%
and they're very inexpensive.

00:15:48.460 --> 00:15:52.150 align:middle line:84%
And it's good because
I'm a very firm believer,

00:15:52.150 --> 00:15:58.000 align:middle line:84%
I would rather have a photocopy
of ancient information

00:15:58.000 --> 00:15:59.480 align:middle line:90%
if I can't have the original.

00:15:59.480 --> 00:16:03.040 align:middle line:84%
It's not about the original,
it's about the information.

00:16:03.040 --> 00:16:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And quite a few of those
have been reprinted.

00:16:08.560 --> 00:16:11.530 align:middle line:90%
Manly Hall died in 1990.

00:16:11.530 --> 00:16:14.770 align:middle line:84%
I might have jumped on a
lot of reprinting of some

00:16:14.770 --> 00:16:16.690 align:middle line:90%
of the alchemical texts.

00:16:16.690 --> 00:16:19.810 align:middle line:84%
But that's not where I was
coming from at the time.

00:16:19.810 --> 00:16:24.790 align:middle line:84%
But what really attracted
me was none of the books,

00:16:24.790 --> 00:16:31.990 align:middle line:84%
but a little notebook that
said, Last Second Material

00:16:31.990 --> 00:16:38.140 align:middle line:84%
Arrived Too Late to Be Included
in the Secret Teaching Book.

00:16:38.140 --> 00:16:40.990 align:middle line:84%
The book, "The Secret
Teaching of All Ages",

00:16:40.990 --> 00:16:44.680 align:middle line:84%
which is magnum opus,
was the greatest book

00:16:44.680 --> 00:16:47.800 align:middle line:84%
of all the books
Manly Hall wrote.

00:16:47.800 --> 00:16:50.050 align:middle line:90%
So that really attracted me.

00:16:50.050 --> 00:16:53.440 align:middle line:84%
But I've got to say that
my spiritual sources

00:16:53.440 --> 00:16:57.880 align:middle line:84%
that led me to say, I want to
go into your private vault,

00:16:57.880 --> 00:16:59.873 align:middle line:90%
directed me to--

00:16:59.873 --> 00:17:01.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To that
notebook for a reason.

00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:02.560 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Exactly.

00:17:02.560 --> 00:17:05.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: First of all, let's
just take the big boy up,

00:17:05.560 --> 00:17:09.040 align:middle line:90%
"Secret Teaching of All Ages".

00:17:09.040 --> 00:17:10.480 align:middle line:90%
And this book is--

00:17:10.480 --> 00:17:12.310 align:middle line:90%
it's so beautiful.

00:17:12.310 --> 00:17:14.839 align:middle line:84%
So this one we
found, for example,

00:17:14.839 --> 00:17:18.970 align:middle line:84%
is the image of as
above, so below.

00:17:18.970 --> 00:17:20.710 align:middle line:10%
And the way he
was able to depict

00:17:20.710 --> 00:17:25.089 align:middle line:10%
this in the magnificent artwork
embedded with the symbolism

00:17:25.089 --> 00:17:27.670 align:middle line:10%
is as important as the text.

00:17:27.670 --> 00:17:33.130 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: And in this notebook
that the information was not

00:17:33.130 --> 00:17:36.880 align:middle line:84%
included, people have
bought this book, which

00:17:36.880 --> 00:17:42.730 align:middle line:84%
was published in 1928, and they
have just read it straight.

00:17:42.730 --> 00:17:49.720 align:middle line:84%
But in the series of lectures
that Manly gave in 1928, which

00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:52.090 align:middle line:84%
were not included
in this book, he

00:17:52.090 --> 00:17:57.640 align:middle line:84%
speaks about how he envisioned
people reading this book,

00:17:57.640 --> 00:18:02.950 align:middle line:84%
and how they were to approach
this book chapter by chapter,

00:18:02.950 --> 00:18:05.020 align:middle line:90%
symbol by symbol.

00:18:05.020 --> 00:18:09.070 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes
this material very, very

00:18:09.070 --> 00:18:12.250 align:middle line:84%
important that I did
find in his vault,

00:18:12.250 --> 00:18:16.660 align:middle line:84%
was that it was talking about
the true intent of the book.

00:18:16.660 --> 00:18:18.520 align:middle line:84%
Now when a book
comes out, you would

00:18:18.520 --> 00:18:21.430 align:middle line:84%
believe the true
intent is somebody

00:18:21.430 --> 00:18:26.630 align:middle line:84%
is sharing information, and
we're satisfied with that.

00:18:26.630 --> 00:18:30.760 align:middle line:84%
But when somebody has writings
about the deeper reasons

00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:33.910 align:middle line:84%
why the book has
been written, you

00:18:33.910 --> 00:18:35.280 align:middle line:90%
would really want to know that.

00:18:35.280 --> 00:18:36.572 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, that's the key.

00:18:36.572 --> 00:18:38.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: It is the key.

00:18:38.080 --> 00:18:44.890 align:middle line:84%
And that is what I found
in these materials is

00:18:44.890 --> 00:18:50.200 align:middle line:84%
his key of saying not only
how to approach the book,

00:18:50.200 --> 00:18:54.490 align:middle line:84%
but within here saying,
the italicized words

00:18:54.490 --> 00:19:01.240 align:middle line:84%
are leading to a mark and
part of the inner teachings

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:03.250 align:middle line:90%
of the inner teachings.

00:19:03.250 --> 00:19:07.270 align:middle line:84%
And that is very, very
profound from an individual

00:19:07.270 --> 00:19:11.560 align:middle line:84%
who had the awareness and
knowledge that Manly Hall had.

00:19:11.560 --> 00:19:18.950 align:middle line:84%
He would give lectures
that he charged $1.00,

00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:23.750 align:middle line:84%
the first time he lectured
until his last lecture.

00:19:23.750 --> 00:19:28.700 align:middle line:84%
When they're typed out,
they're 15 pages single spaced,

00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:30.350 align:middle line:90%
and he never used notes.

00:19:30.350 --> 00:19:32.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:32.210 --> 00:19:33.200 align:middle line:90%
That was like Steiner.

00:19:33.200 --> 00:19:35.630 align:middle line:84%
Just streamed it,
just streamed it.

00:19:35.630 --> 00:19:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: And so here,
when he's talking

00:19:38.300 --> 00:19:42.320 align:middle line:84%
about the big book
and these materials,

00:19:42.320 --> 00:19:47.060 align:middle line:84%
for those individuals
who are not only into him

00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:49.220 align:middle line:84%
and have got the
book, but people

00:19:49.220 --> 00:19:52.280 align:middle line:84%
who are studying and
learning in this field,

00:19:52.280 --> 00:19:54.290 align:middle line:90%
it's very important to have.

00:19:54.290 --> 00:19:56.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So essentially
what he was saying

00:19:56.330 --> 00:19:59.870 align:middle line:84%
is that if you read this
book with the understanding

00:19:59.870 --> 00:20:03.230 align:middle line:84%
that when you see
italicized words or phrases,

00:20:03.230 --> 00:20:05.120 align:middle line:90%
you're being given a symbol.

00:20:05.120 --> 00:20:06.200 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Exactly.

00:20:06.200 --> 00:20:08.930 align:middle line:84%
And then it goes
deeper by saying

00:20:08.930 --> 00:20:10.790 align:middle line:84%
people are not
really understanding

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:15.170 align:middle line:90%
what symbols are meant to do.

00:20:15.170 --> 00:20:19.760 align:middle line:84%
There is a little bit more to
symbols than people realize.

00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:24.080 align:middle line:84%
The ancients set up the
symbols in their time

00:20:24.080 --> 00:20:29.450 align:middle line:84%
to evoke things having to do
with the mind, the spirit.

00:20:29.450 --> 00:20:31.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Access
between dimensions.

00:20:31.100 --> 00:20:32.150 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Exactly.

00:20:32.150 --> 00:20:35.420 align:middle line:84%
And what's happened is over
time, when people start

00:20:35.420 --> 00:20:39.650 align:middle line:84%
attaching their
analysis of a symbol,

00:20:39.650 --> 00:20:43.790 align:middle line:84%
it starts changing from what
those original symbols really

00:20:43.790 --> 00:20:47.840 align:middle line:84%
were meant to be sharing with
individuals who would be gazing

00:20:47.840 --> 00:20:52.430 align:middle line:84%
because it's about how
we observe anything

00:20:52.430 --> 00:20:53.900 align:middle line:90%
that is very important.

00:20:53.900 --> 00:20:58.280 align:middle line:84%
And basically what
these pages were,

00:20:58.280 --> 00:21:05.690 align:middle line:84%
Manly Hall intended to put the
pages here into the big book.

00:21:05.690 --> 00:21:09.860 align:middle line:84%
But they weren't able to
get in because they arrived

00:21:09.860 --> 00:21:12.560 align:middle line:90%
at the printer too late.

00:21:12.560 --> 00:21:15.800 align:middle line:84%
So then he thought,
OK, I have some pages.

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:18.600 align:middle line:84%
I might as well turn
them into lectures.

00:21:18.600 --> 00:21:23.030 align:middle line:84%
So here we have 20
lectures elaborating

00:21:23.030 --> 00:21:27.920 align:middle line:84%
further upon where he might
have had one page in the book,

00:21:27.920 --> 00:21:33.620 align:middle line:84%
there's now three or four pages
with a more full-blown lecture

00:21:33.620 --> 00:21:35.970 align:middle line:90%
on a particular topic.

00:21:35.970 --> 00:21:37.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: This is not edited.

00:21:37.220 --> 00:21:40.840 align:middle line:84%
This is in his original,
typewritten on a typewriter

00:21:40.840 --> 00:21:41.640 align:middle line:90%
documents.

00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:42.440 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Yes.

00:21:42.440 --> 00:21:44.990 align:middle line:90%
Exactly how I found it.

00:21:44.990 --> 00:21:48.320 align:middle line:84%
What I did was I
put an introduction.

00:21:48.320 --> 00:21:53.960 align:middle line:84%
I have not even commented
on any of the materials

00:21:53.960 --> 00:21:56.120 align:middle line:84%
other than what you
and I are doing now,

00:21:56.120 --> 00:22:01.760 align:middle line:84%
purely because I don't think
we should always accept

00:22:01.760 --> 00:22:05.330 align:middle line:84%
somebody else's
analysis, what they

00:22:05.330 --> 00:22:07.130 align:middle line:90%
believe something is saying.

00:22:07.130 --> 00:22:08.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're
talking about something

00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:14.130 align:middle line:84%
that is really more a matter of
consumption versus engagement.

00:22:14.130 --> 00:22:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And I think we are a
consumptive species right now.

00:22:16.790 --> 00:22:18.990 align:middle line:90%
We've been led to be consumers.

00:22:18.990 --> 00:22:21.500 align:middle line:84%
So it's a kind of a
double-edged sword

00:22:21.500 --> 00:22:25.010 align:middle line:84%
in a way, in that you have
all this incredible ability

00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:27.950 align:middle line:84%
to access ancient
teachings of all kinds

00:22:27.950 --> 00:22:30.290 align:middle line:84%
from throughout the ages
because of the internet.

00:22:30.290 --> 00:22:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And if you're going to do snail
mail way because of libraries,

00:22:34.560 --> 00:22:37.130 align:middle line:84%
the one or two in the world
that exist like yours,

00:22:37.130 --> 00:22:39.170 align:middle line:90%
people can get that information.

00:22:39.170 --> 00:22:41.940 align:middle line:84%
It's there for us
to engage with.

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:45.200 align:middle line:84%
But instead, it's easy,
oftentimes, to say, oh--

00:22:45.200 --> 00:22:46.550 align:middle line:90%
I fall prey to it.

00:22:46.550 --> 00:22:47.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm guilty of it myself.

00:22:47.810 --> 00:22:49.965 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I saw an interview
with so-and-so.

00:22:49.965 --> 00:22:50.840 align:middle line:90%
That was really cool.

00:22:50.840 --> 00:22:53.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to incorporate
that into my own stuff.

00:22:53.150 --> 00:22:54.990 align:middle line:90%
It's really easy to do that.

00:22:54.990 --> 00:22:57.530 align:middle line:84%
But it's hard to actually
sit down and take the time

00:22:57.530 --> 00:23:00.200 align:middle line:84%
to engage to where
your life becomes

00:23:00.200 --> 00:23:03.770 align:middle line:84%
this more fulsome expression
of these principles.

00:23:03.770 --> 00:23:07.610 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: And what I would
love for your audience

00:23:07.610 --> 00:23:13.580 align:middle line:84%
