00:37:06.620 --> 00:37:10.520 align:middle line:84%
When one is perceiving
or apperceiving

00:37:10.520 --> 00:37:15.320 align:middle line:84%
the essence, the light
beings that we are,

00:37:15.320 --> 00:37:18.890 align:middle line:84%
they are not as inclined to
look at the substance, which

00:37:18.890 --> 00:37:25.610 align:middle line:84%
is the color, the
hair, or no hair.

00:37:25.610 --> 00:37:28.040 align:middle line:84%
They are looking
at pure essence.

00:37:28.040 --> 00:37:33.590 align:middle line:84%
The substance of the spirit
is bringing us to essence.

00:37:33.590 --> 00:37:38.420 align:middle line:84%
The substance of the mind
is generally physical,

00:37:38.420 --> 00:37:41.960 align:middle line:90%
the size, the color.

00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:44.490 align:middle line:90%
We want to look beyond that.

00:37:44.490 --> 00:37:47.390 align:middle line:84%
And if we were looking
at that, this world

00:37:47.390 --> 00:37:50.960 align:middle line:84%
would be quite
different than it is

00:37:50.960 --> 00:37:54.710 align:middle line:84%
right now because we
have actually taken 10

00:37:54.710 --> 00:37:56.960 align:middle line:90%
steps backward, in my opinion.

00:37:56.960 --> 00:38:02.510 align:middle line:84%
There is more segmenting,
more separation, more

00:38:02.510 --> 00:38:06.530 align:middle line:84%
taking it away, forgetting that
everybody bleeds the same color

00:38:06.530 --> 00:38:09.890 align:middle line:84%
right now, which is not
the light of the spirit,

00:38:09.890 --> 00:38:12.350 align:middle line:84%
but that is still a
physical substance.

00:38:12.350 --> 00:38:14.900 align:middle line:90%
Hey, we're of the same blood.

00:38:14.900 --> 00:38:17.720 align:middle line:90%
But we're just far away.

00:38:17.720 --> 00:38:20.150 align:middle line:84%
So the substance of
mind, the substance

00:38:20.150 --> 00:38:22.640 align:middle line:90%
is spirit are vastly different.

00:38:22.640 --> 00:38:25.550 align:middle line:90%
And we can arrive there.

00:38:25.550 --> 00:38:29.090 align:middle line:84%
So the substance
of spirit goes back

00:38:29.090 --> 00:38:35.120 align:middle line:84%
to the essences of objects,
of people, of nature.

00:38:35.120 --> 00:38:38.630 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
this lecture that he

00:38:38.630 --> 00:38:44.060 align:middle line:84%
gave was trying to present
to people, that yes,

00:38:44.060 --> 00:38:48.020 align:middle line:84%
the conditioning is you
look at it from your mind.

00:38:48.020 --> 00:38:55.650 align:middle line:84%
Where you want to get back to
is the essence of the spirit.

00:38:55.650 --> 00:38:59.610 align:middle line:84%
The substance of
spirit is light,

00:38:59.610 --> 00:39:02.850 align:middle line:84%
and you want to be
apperceiving everything

00:39:02.850 --> 00:39:05.340 align:middle line:90%
in its light essence.

00:39:05.340 --> 00:39:06.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So beautifully said.

00:39:06.660 --> 00:39:09.930 align:middle line:84%
And Steven, we brought this up
in other shows, but all of this

00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:13.692 align:middle line:84%
comes into the abilities
that we will understand--

00:39:13.692 --> 00:39:15.150 align:middle line:84%
we should understand
now, in fact--

00:39:15.150 --> 00:39:17.220 align:middle line:84%
that we all innately
possess that we will

00:39:17.220 --> 00:39:20.310 align:middle line:90%
be expressing in the future.

00:39:20.310 --> 00:39:23.730 align:middle line:84%
The material world is
not what we think it is.

00:39:23.730 --> 00:39:25.620 align:middle line:90%
It's immaterial in nature.

00:39:25.620 --> 00:39:29.160 align:middle line:84%
How are our minds and our
hearts and our emotions function

00:39:29.160 --> 00:39:33.210 align:middle line:84%
can program outcomes that have
a material effect, but are

00:39:33.210 --> 00:39:34.800 align:middle line:90%
of a nonmaterial nature.

00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:38.340 align:middle line:84%
And this-- I've said this
before in other shows--

00:39:38.340 --> 00:39:40.560 align:middle line:84%
you developed
somewhere along the way

00:39:40.560 --> 00:39:44.460 align:middle line:84%
the ability to assist people
in their healing process, which

00:39:44.460 --> 00:39:47.580 align:middle line:84%
is very condensed
and quick process

00:39:47.580 --> 00:39:50.460 align:middle line:84%
you go to if a person
sincerely wishes to reverse

00:39:50.460 --> 00:39:52.355 align:middle line:90%
the imbalance in their body.

00:39:52.355 --> 00:39:54.730 align:middle line:84%
And you've dealt with many,
many, many, many, many people

00:39:54.730 --> 00:39:56.310 align:middle line:84%
in every single
kind of condition.

00:39:56.310 --> 00:39:57.480 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: But you know why?

00:39:57.480 --> 00:39:58.805 align:middle line:90%
Because I love them.

00:39:58.805 --> 00:40:00.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You love
them, exactly.

00:40:00.180 --> 00:40:03.210 align:middle line:84%
You have this heart that I
said at the very beginning.

00:40:03.210 --> 00:40:06.450 align:middle line:84%
You have this heart energy
that comes out and meets

00:40:06.450 --> 00:40:09.190 align:middle line:84%
with their desire
to be whole again.

00:40:09.190 --> 00:40:12.210 align:middle line:84%
And in that, you work
through nonmaterial means,

00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:15.660 align:middle line:84%
pure information, pure
space, like a black hole,

00:40:15.660 --> 00:40:19.530 align:middle line:84%
reprogram it, and health
resumes in these people.

00:40:19.530 --> 00:40:23.850 align:middle line:84%
And that's not what we're
talking about directly.

00:40:23.850 --> 00:40:25.620 align:middle line:84%
That is the extension
of what we're all

00:40:25.620 --> 00:40:29.880 align:middle line:84%
capable of if we can understand
the essence of our true nature,

00:40:29.880 --> 00:40:31.660 align:middle line:84%
which is one thing
we're capable of.

00:40:31.660 --> 00:40:32.460 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: Right.

00:40:32.460 --> 00:40:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And again, why I think this
is pertinent is if somebody

00:40:36.570 --> 00:40:40.410 align:middle line:84%
is going to be
pointing the way, you

00:40:40.410 --> 00:40:45.780 align:middle line:84%
would want them to point you in
the safest direction possible

00:40:45.780 --> 00:40:47.580 align:middle line:84%
that will get you
where you want to go.

00:40:47.580 --> 00:40:52.650 align:middle line:84%
That is, again, why I have
admired Manly Hall's material,

00:40:52.650 --> 00:40:58.600 align:middle line:84%
is he is doing in its pure
form rather than saying,

00:40:58.600 --> 00:41:01.975 align:middle line:84%
well, OK, I read this,
and this is what I feel,

00:41:01.975 --> 00:41:02.850 align:middle line:90%
and I'm pointing you.

00:41:02.850 --> 00:41:05.550 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:41:05.550 --> 00:41:10.320 align:middle line:84%
This just pure, this is
what you want to go towards.

00:41:10.320 --> 00:41:13.650 align:middle line:84%
It is, again, when I talk
about an example of Plato

00:41:13.650 --> 00:41:16.260 align:middle line:90%
and Aristotle.

00:41:16.260 --> 00:41:18.900 align:middle line:84%
Aristotle's complaint
with Plato was

00:41:18.900 --> 00:41:22.140 align:middle line:84%
he's not telling you
exactly how to get,

00:41:22.140 --> 00:41:27.030 align:middle line:84%
if the end result
is this glass, Plato

00:41:27.030 --> 00:41:30.660 align:middle line:84%
would just be telling you, you
want to arrive at this glass.

00:41:30.660 --> 00:41:32.940 align:middle line:84%
For Aristotle in the
scientific approach,

00:41:32.940 --> 00:41:34.720 align:middle line:84%
it's how exactly
do you get there?

00:41:34.720 --> 00:41:35.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He wants
the mechanical model

00:41:35.010 --> 00:41:35.910 align:middle line:90%
for how you get there.

00:41:35.910 --> 00:41:37.118 align:middle line:90%
>>ROSS: How do you get there?

00:41:37.118 --> 00:41:40.140 align:middle line:84%
How many miles, how many
feet, how many inches?

00:41:40.140 --> 00:41:44.220 align:middle line:84%
Then you are locked into
that particular approach.

00:41:44.220 --> 00:41:47.290 align:middle line:84%
I enjoy-- Manly Hall
is not the only one--

00:41:47.290 --> 00:41:49.550 align:middle line:84%
there's other great
philosophers--

00:41:49.550 --> 00:41:54.090 align:middle line:84%
the less that they put
their own spin on something.

00:41:54.090 --> 00:41:58.050 align:middle line:84%
And now let's go into even
what's happening in the world.

00:41:58.050 --> 00:42:03.280 align:middle line:84%
If each one of these stations
puts their own spin, all we do

00:42:03.280 --> 00:42:04.080 align:middle line:90%
is spin.

00:42:04.080 --> 00:42:06.060 align:middle line:84%
You turn the TV, you
get this channel.

00:42:06.060 --> 00:42:07.477 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everyone's
spinning out.

00:42:07.477 --> 00:42:09.750 align:middle line:84%
>>ROSS: It's spinning,
spinning, spinning, spinning.

00:42:09.750 --> 00:42:12.150 align:middle line:84%
You know what somebody
should go down to?

00:42:12.150 --> 00:42:14.670 align:middle line:90%
Empathy, love.

00:42:14.670 --> 00:42:17.070 align:middle line:84%
Maybe this sounds
trite, but if people

00:42:17.070 --> 00:42:19.170 align:middle line:84%
are claiming that
they're religious,

00:42:19.170 --> 00:42:21.570 align:middle line:90%
go back to the teachings.

00:42:21.570 --> 00:42:23.790 align:middle line:90%
Empathy, love.

00:42:23.790 --> 00:42:25.210 align:middle line:90%
Help thy neighbor.

00:42:25.210 --> 00:42:30.060 align:middle line:84%
Now ask yourself, one should
ask themselves, who is doing it,

00:42:30.060 --> 00:42:31.220 align:middle line:90%
and am I doing it?

00:42:31.220 --> 00:42:32.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:42:32.310 --> 00:42:34.710 align:middle line:84%
And this is something,
too, when you're

00:42:34.710 --> 00:42:37.140 align:middle line:84%
talking about the notion of
putting the principle out

00:42:37.140 --> 00:42:39.160 align:middle line:84%
